    "# Auto-Encoder Example with MNIST Dataset\n",
    "This notebook provides a step-by-step guide to building an auto-encoder using the MNIST dataset."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Introduction\n",
    "An auto-encoder is a type of artificial neural network used to learn efficient codings of unlabeled data. It is primarily used for dimensionality reduction, feature learning, and anomaly detection. The network consists of two parts: an encoder that compresses the input into a latent-space representation, and a decoder that reconstructs the input from the latent space."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Steps of Auto-Encoder\n",
    "1. **Data Preparation**: Load and preprocess the data.\n",
    "2. **Model Architecture**: Define the encoder and decoder architecture.\n",
    "3. **Training**: Train the auto-encoder model on the data.\n",
    "4. **Evaluation**: Evaluate the model's performance.\n",
    "5. **Visualization**: Visualize the results."
   ]
  },
